liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Australian dollar is taking a hit today on signs the Chinese economy is slowing down. The local currency fell 0.5 per cent to 64.85 US cents, the lowest since November last year. That's after it jumped to 65.38 US cents after April's hotter than expected inflation numbers, which increased expectations of a rate rise by the RBA next week.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Australian dollar falls to lowest since November

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: As you've hearing, RBA governor Philip Lowe appeared before a Senate Estimates hearing this morning. He said PwC was working for the RBA to advise on worker underpayments. The ABC also hired PwC to do a review of underpayments to thousands of workers. Mr Lowe slammed PwC's tax leaks as "appalling" and says PwC is banned from future RBA work. Here's senior business correspondent Peter Ryan.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: RBA governor says PwC banned from future contracts

children.content: As you've hearing, RBA governor Philip Lowe appeared before a Senate Estimates hearing this morning.
He said PwC was working for the RBA to advise on worker underpayments.
The ABC also hired PwC to do a review of underpayments to thousands of workers.
Mr Lowe slammed PwC's tax leaks as "appalling" and says PwC is banned from future RBA work.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Tech giant Atlassian says companies aren't doing enough to reduce their carbon footprint. The software firm aims to achieve net zero emissions by 2040, mainly by reducing emissions rather than using offsets. It has written a guide for other companies to follow, and it's warned they can't depend on offsets to meet the majority of their carbon reduction targets. I spoke to Jess Hyman, head of sustainability, at Atlassian for ABC News Channel.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Atlassian says business not doing enough to reduce pollution
